node.text: There are of corse some dress codes that make sence like high visibility clothing and savety shoes. But high heels - realy? Even if you like wearing high heels every orthopedist will tell you - dont wear them all day under long periods. It's causing pain, postural defects and destroy your feet. If your employer kann force you to damage your health because you happened to be a woman it's not fair. This rules should be banned. There are so many nice alternatives to high heels...
@estheranditasari

Why are people talking about high heels? Clue: it’s to do with sexism.
...
Have you heard of #KuToo? 🇯🇵 It’s a campaign in Japan calling for laws to stop forcing women to wear high heels at work 👠
...
Actor Yumi Ishikawa started the movement. She handed in a government petition with nearly 19,000 signatures asking for a ban on dress codes. 😮
...
It’s on the grounds of sexual discrimination and harassment. She says it’s the “first step forward”. 👣
...
She also said she’d like “social perceptions to change so that women wearing formal flat shoes becomes standard.” 🥿
...
What do you think? Should your boss be able to decide what you wear to work? Comment below! 🤔👇🏼
...

@rivoltasata 🙌🏾! Out of interest, what’s your preferred footwear for work? Do you ever feel pressure to dress a certain way, or do you just wear what you want? 💖
@bbcminute I work for my self and wear what I like, blessed for the privilege ✊🏾
Great work! Free those feet!
@_fightforfeminism_ Thanks for sharing your thoughts! Have you ever been told what to wear at work? 🤔
Your boss shouldn't be able to dictate your clothing preferences. 👏👏Free the feet!
@fe_lopez 👋
@camila.estilo pauta boa💛
Professional footwear requirement, good. Painful footwear requirement, bad. A man can look professional in flat shoes, and so can a woman.
@the_asian_activist Thanks so much for your comment 👍 Have you ever had to wear heels for work?

It is completely sexist to demand women to wear shoes which are also painful, but simply the act of controlling women’s choice of attire is wrong. It’s not about being professional because a dress and a suit/blazer is also professional. Telling women to do something is setting the standard that it’s okay to expect one gender to wear certain shoes and not the other. It’s normalising government and company control over women, just like in Alabama and other states women have been restricted the right to control their own bodies. It’s a step in the WRONG direction.

Your boss should not be able to tell you what to wear. However, for each role and each working environment, people should be clued on and able to decide what’s appropriate for their working environment.

Heels are perceived to be the appropriate female corporate complement. But it’s an highly uncomfortable piece of footwear. An employee who craves maximum productivity regardless of gender should not put forward tiles that’s promotes inconvenience.
Of course NOT!!!! The only person who should decide what you should wear is yourself!!!! Period.
@plainettes
